<theme id="thm219">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Dotted 8th note</title>
<tocimage>img219.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson the dotted 8th note pattern in simple times is introduced:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (Metrica 2 4 noVisible)
           (n * c. g+)(n * s g-)(Barra Doble))
        (c (n * n l)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-)(Barra Doble))
        (c (n * c g+)(n * c l g-)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>
<para>Note how the rhythm of dotted 8th note can be obtained from one 8th note and
two 16th notes, when tying the 8th note.</para>
<para>Always that you find a trouble with a rhythmic pattern, 
study it first without the ties. When learned without the ties it will be easier to
learn the original one with ties.</para>


<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (Metrica 2 8)
           (n * c g+)(n * s)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * c l g+)(n * s)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * c. g+)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * s g+)(n * s)(n * s)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * s l g+)(n * s)(n * s)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * c g+)(n * s)(n * s g-)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score></para>

<para>In a similar way you can get and learn the other patterns of this lesson:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (Metrica 2 8)
           (n * n)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * n l)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * c g+)(n * c g-)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-))
        (c (n * c g+)(n * c l g-)(n * c. g+)(n * s g-)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score></para>
</part>


